    "reasoning": "First, determine the value of $k$. The polynomial $x^2 - ax + a$ has an integer root $r$. Substituting $r$ gives $r^2 - ar + a = 0$, so $a = \\frac{r^2}{r - 1}$. For $a$ to be a positive integer, $r - 1$ must divide $r^2$. Rewriting $a = r + 1 + \\frac{1}{r - 1}$, $\\frac{1}{r - 1}$ must be an integer, so $r - 1 = \\pm 1$. This gives $r = 2$ (yielding $a = 4$) or $r = 0$ (yielding $a = 0$, invalid as $a$ must be positive). Thus, $a = 4$ is the only valid solution, so $k = a + 7 = 11$.\n\nNext, analyze the dice probabilities. Let $p_i$ be the probability of rolling $i$ on one die. Given $\\text{P}(\\text{sum} = 2) = p_1^2 = 0.04$, so $p_1 = 0.2$. Similarly, $\\text{P}(\\text{sum} = 12) = p_6^2 = 0.01$, so $p_6 = 0.1$. The sum $k = 11$ occurs for pairs $(5,6)$ and $(6,5)$, so its probability is $2p_5p_6 = 0.2p_5$. To maximize this, maximize $p_5$ under the constraint $p_1 + p_2 + p_3 + p_4 + p_5 + p_6 = 1$. Substituting known values, $p_2 + p_3 + p_4 + p_5 = 0.7$. The maximum $p_5 = 0.7$ (when $p_2 = p_3 = p_4 = 0$) gives $\\text{P}(\\text{sum} = 11) = 0.2 \\times 0.7 = 0.14$. Thus, $\\lfloor 100 \\times 0.14 \\rfloor = 14$.",
    "answer": "14"
